{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"afc813a93835b7863","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are scanning ~/dharma_swarm/ for architecture documentation, agent definitions, and gate systems.\n\nSearch for:\n1. Agent definitions — any YAML, JSON, or Python files defining agent types, capabilities, personalities\n   - Look in dharma_swarm/agents/, dharma_swarm/config/, or similar\n   - The founding-agents.yaml for telos-engine needs this\n2. Gate systems — telos gates, dharmic gates, quality gates\n   - hooks/telos_gate.py\n   - Any other gate implementations\n   - Gate configuration files\n3. Architecture documentation\n   - Any docs/ or architecture/ directory\n   - Design decision records\n   - System diagrams or descriptions\n4. The Darwin Engine — evolution archive, fitness criteria, selection mechanisms\n   - dharma_swarm/darwin_engine.py or similar\n5. The Shakti framework — what are the four Shaktis and how are they implemented?\n6. Colony intelligence patterns — how agents coordinate\n7. The 5-layer architecture: models → providers → agent_runner → orchestrator → swarm\n   - Read the top of each file for docstrings explaining the layer's purpose\n8. ecosystem_map.py — the 42 paths, 6 domains\n\nFor each finding, report:\n- Full path\n- Key architectural concepts\n- Where it maps to in telos-engine/ (architecture/agents/, architecture/gates/, seeds/)\n- Design rationale (WHY, not just WHAT)\n\nDO NOT write any code or create any files. This is RESEARCH ONLY."},"uuid":"043c1dca-9d68-4835-8262-79242b257a47","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:05.280Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
