{"parentUuid":"aa0c069d-3917-4128-a886-ea7d3e65f03c","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afc813a93835b7863","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:Read","command":"callback"},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01SDWFN6V86Aata5sVppBjMs","toolUseID":"toolu_01SDWFN6V86Aata5sVppBjMs","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:31.375Z","uuid":"4726a1e8-d89d-42c6-8fe3-b00fcb6277a8","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"519769d9-5d6b-4eb0-bbd3-f39bb83c9e36","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eb82f461-7131-4c9b-87e7-a8beab163db0","agentId":"afc813a93835b7863","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SDWFN6V86Aata5sVppBjMs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Dharma Corpus Schema\n     2→## Versioned Dharma Corpus — Schema Definition, Update Protocol, and Reference Entries\n     3→**DHARMA SWARM System | Constitutional Layer 2 of 3**\n     4→**Document Version:** 1.0.0\n     5→**Status:** Active\n     6→**Last Updated:** 2026-03-05T17:16:00+09:00\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## Table of Contents\n    11→\n    12→1. [Overview and Position in the Constitutional Stack](#1-overview-and-position-in-the-constitutional-stack)\n    13→2. [Corpus Entry Schema](#2-corpus-entry-schema)\n    14→   - 2.1 [Field Definitions](#21-field-definitions)\n    15→   - 2.2 [YAML Schema](#22-yaml-schema)\n    16→   - 2.3 [JSON Schema (machine-readable)](#23-json-schema-machine-readable)\n    17→3. [Update and Review Protocol](#3-update-and-review-protocol)\n    18→   - 3.1 [Adding a New Entry](#31-adding-a-new-entry)\n    19→   - 3.2 [Modifying an Existing Entry](#32-modifying-an-existing-entry)\n    20→   - 3.3 [Deprecating an Entry](#33-deprecating-an-entry)\n    21→   - 3.4 [Emergency Overrides](#34-emergency-overrides)\n    22→4. [Conflict Resolution Protocol](#4-conflict-resolution-protocol)\n    23→5. [Example Corpus Entries](#5-example-corpus-entries)\n    24→   - DC-2025-0001: Kernel Mutation Sandbox Isolation\n    25→   - DC-2025-0002: Client Data Confidentiality\n    26→   - DC-2025-0003: Agent Spawn Depth Limit\n    27→   - DC-2025-0004: R_V Metric Acceptance Threshold\n    28→   - DC-2025-0005: Learned Constraint — Post-Optimization R_V Verification\n    29→   - DC-2025-0006: Self-Evolution Scope Boundaries\n    30→   - DC-2025-0007: Compute Budget Hard Cap\n    31→   - DC-2025-0008: Client Deliverable Quality Gate\n    32→   - DC-2025-0009: Outreach Email Capability Representation\n    33→   - DC-2025-0010: Numerical Precision Preservation\n    34→6. [Querying the Corpus](#6-querying-the-corpus)\n    35→   - 6.1 [Query Interface Specification](#61-query-interface-specification)\n    36→   - 6.2 [Conflict Detection Query](#62-conflict-detection-query)\n    37→   - 6.3 [Policy Compiler Integration](#63-policy-compiler-integration)\n    38→7. [Corpus Maintenance Notes](#7-corpus-maintenance-notes)\n    39→\n    40→---\n    41→\n    42→## 1. Overview and Position in the Constitutional Stack\n    43→\n    44→The **Versioned Dharma Corpus** is Constitutional Layer 2 of 3 in the DHARMA SWARM system. It sits between the immutable axioms of the Meta-Dharma and the runtime decisions produced by the Contextual Policy Compiler.\n    45→\n    46→```\n    47→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    48→│  Layer 1: Immutable Meta-Dharma                         │\n    49→│  ~10 axioms. Never change. Ground truth.                │\n    50→│  Source: Dharma_Constitution_v0.md                      │\n    51→└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘\n    52→                        │ derived from\n    53→┌───────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────┐\n    54→│  Layer 2: Versioned Dharma Corpus  ◄── THIS DOCUMENT    │\n    55→│  Mutable. Domain rules, policies, learned constraints.  │\n    56→│  Versioned. Audited. Gate-controlled.                   │\n    57→└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘\n    58→                        │ compiled with runtime context\n    59→┌───────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────┐\n    60→│  Layer 3: Contextual Policy Compiler                    │\n    61→│  Axioms + Corpus + Context → Runtime Decision           │\n    62→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    63→```\n    64→\n    65→**Design principle:** The Corpus is case law built on constitutional law. Every entry must trace to a Meta-Dharma axiom. No entry can contradict the axioms. Entries can be added, versioned, or deprecated, but never deleted — the full history is preserved as audit trail. The Corpus is the *living law* of the swarm.\n    66→\n    67→**Corpus categories:**\n    68→| Category | Description |\n    69→|---|---|\n    70→| `safety` | Rules preventing harm, data loss, or unsafe system states |\n    71→| `ethics` | Guidelines for morally appropriate agent behavior |\n    72→| `operational` | System-level rules governing resource use, spawn limits, timing |\n    73→| `domain-specific` | Rules tied to a particular technical domain (e.g., GPU kernels) |\n    74→| `learned-constraint` | Rules derived from post-incident analysis or observed failure modes |\n    75→\n    76→---\n    77→\n    78→## 2. Corpus Entry Schema\n    79→\n    80→### 2.1 Field Definitions\n    81→\n    82→| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n    83→|---|---|---|---|\n    84→| `id` | string | yes | Unique identifier. Format: `DC-YYYY-NNNN`. Immutable after creation. |\n    85→| `version` | string | yes | Semantic version of this entry (`MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`). Increment on each revision. |\n    86→| `status` | enum | yes | Lifecycle state. See status lifecycle below. |\n    87→| `category` | enum | yes | One of: `safety`, `ethics`, `operational`, `domain-specific`, `learned-constraint` |\n    88→| `scope` | object | yes | Specifies which layers, agent types, and contexts this entry applies to. |\n    89→| `rule` | string | yes | The rule in plain human-readable language. Authoritative statement of intent. |\n    90→| `formal_constraint` | string | yes | Machine-parsable expression of the rule. Uses structured pseudo-code. |\n    91→| `rationale` | string | yes | Explanation of *why* this rule exists. Reason-based, following Anthropic's constitutional pattern. |\n    92→| `evidence` | array | yes | Links to incidents, research, metrics, or reasoning that justify the rule. |\n    93→| `parent_axiom` | array | yes | One or more Meta-Dharma axiom IDs this entry derives from. |\n    94→| `conflict_resolution` | string | no | Instructions for resolving conflicts with other corpus entries. |\n    95→| `severity` | enum | yes | `critical`, `high`, `medium`, `low`. Determines enforcement strictness and conflict priority. |\n    96→| `enforcement` | enum | yes | `block`, `warn`, `log`, `gate_human`, `gate_steelman`. How violations are handled. |\n    97→| `created_by` | string | yes | Identity of creator: human email or agent ID (e.g., `agent:orchestrator-v2`). |\n    98→| `created_at` | string | yes | ISO 8601 timestamp of initial creation. Immutable. |\n    99→| `review_history` | array | yes | Ordered array of review records. Each records reviewer, outcome, timestamp, notes. |\n   100→| `supersedes` | string | no | ID of the entry this entry replaces. Null if original. |\n   101→| `superseded_by` | string | no | ID of entry that replaced this one. Set when this entry is deprecated. |\n   102→| `tags` | array | yes | Free-form searchable strings for indexing and filtering. |\n   103→| `expiry` | string | no | ISO 8601 date. If set, entry auto-transitions to `deprecated` at this date. |\n   104→\n   105→**Status lifecycle:**\n   106→\n   107→```\n   108→draft → proposed → gated → active → deprecated\n   109→                                  ↘ superseded\n   110→```\n   111→\n   112→| Status | Meaning |\n   113→|---|---|\n   114→| `draft` | Initial proposal, not yet submitted for review |\n   115→| `proposed` | Submitted for gate review process |\n   116→| `gated` | Passed all three gates, awaiting human sign-off |\n   117→| `active` | Approved and enforced at runtime |\n   118→| `deprecated` | No longer enforced; retained for audit trail |\n   119→| `superseded` | Replaced by a newer entry; retained for audit trail |\n   120→\n   121→**Enforcement levels:**\n   122→\n   123→| Enforcement | Behavior |\n   124→|---|---|\n   125→| `block` | Hard stop. Agent action is prevented. Error returned. |\n   126→| `warn` | Action proceeds but a structured warning is logged and surfaced. |\n   127→| `log` | Action proceeds; violation is silently recorded for review. |\n   128→| `gate_human` | Execution pauses; a human operator must approve before proceeding. |\n   129→| `gate_steelman` | Execution pauses; an adversarial agent constructs the best counter-argument, then human reviews both argument and counter. |\n   130→\n   131→---\n   132→\n   133→### 2.2 YAML Schema\n   134→\n   135→The canonical on-disk representation of a corpus entry is YAML. The following is the annotated schema template:\n   136→\n   137→```yaml\n   138→# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   139→# DHARMA CORPUS ENTRY — Schema Template v1.0\n   140→# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   141→id: \"DC-YYYY-NNNN\"                # Immutable. Assigned on first commit.\n   142→version: \"1.0.0\"                  # Semantic version. Increment on revision.\n   143→status: draft                     # draft | proposed | gated | active | deprecated | superseded\n   144→\n   145→category: safety                  # safety | ethics | operational | domain-specific | learned-constraint\n   146→\n   147→scope:\n   148→  layers:                         # Which constitutional layers this applies to\n   149→    - policy_compiler\n   150→    - corpus_writer"}]},"uuid":"f5e90b8d-e5e5-4810-b269-13ffd99e14fa","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:31.374Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"519769d9-5d6b-4eb0-bbd3-f39bb83c9e36","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
