{"parentUuid":"5f5f1174-13d0-489f-b521-f6d54895046c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"0fd463d9-b82e-40a5-90f7-91f9435b3a86","agentId":"afc813a93835b7863","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U8UN5J6RYLRAyFrauUENYG","type":"tool_result","content":"total 136\n-rw-r--r--@   1 dhyana  staff    596 Mar 14 21:27 __init__.py\ndrwxr-xr-x@   9 dhyana  staff    288 Mar 15 01:34 __pycache__\ndrwxr-xr-x@  10 dhyana  staff    320 Mar 15 01:30 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 207 dhyana  staff   6624 Mar 15 20:52 ..\n-rw-r--r--@   1 dhyana  staff  11224 Mar 15 01:01 code.py\n-rw-r--r--@   1 dhyana  staff   5517 Mar 15 01:02 common.py\n-rw-r--r--@   1 dhyana  staff   5118 Mar 15 01:01 meta.py\n-rw-r--r--@   1 dhyana  staff  10847 Mar 15 01:30 product.py\n-rw-r--r--@   1 dhyana  staff  12035 Mar 15 01:18 research.py\n-rw-r--r--@   1 dhyana  staff   9438 Mar 15 01:01 skill.py","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"f18d8ae8-a741-4f79-81da-6d8f5f6e2047","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:47:41.104Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5f5f1174-13d0-489f-b521-f6d54895046c","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"f18d8ae8-a741-4f79-81da-6d8f5f6e2047","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afc813a93835b7863","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01T1AuH5fijc2xoTKFJpL4a7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have enough information to create a comprehensive architectural scan. Let me compile the findings:\n\n---\n\n## DHARMA SWARM — COMPREHENSIVE ARCHITECTURAL SCAN\n\nBased on extensive exploration of `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/`, here is the complete architecture documentation mapping to telos-engine requirements:\n\n### 1. AGENT DEFINITIONS & CAPABILITIES\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/startup_crew.py` — Default agent fleet configuration\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/models.py` (lines 43-56) — AgentRole enum\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/.claude/agents/browser/browser-agent.yaml` — YAML agent spec example\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/autonomous_agent.py` — ReAct-loop agent implementation\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/persistent_agent.py` — Stateful agent wrapper\n\n**Agent Roles (defined in models.py):**\n```\nCODER, REVIEWER, RESEARCHER, TESTER, ORCHESTRATOR, GENERAL,\nCARTOGRAPHER, ARCHEOLOGIST, SURGEON, ARCHITECT, VALIDATOR, CONDUCTOR\n```\n\n**Default Crew Architecture (startup_crew.py):**\n- **Skill-driven**: Reads SKILL.md files from ~/.claude/skills/ dynamically\n- **Fallback to DEFAULT_CREW** if no skills found\n- **Multi-provider strategy**:\n  - OpenRouter preferred (if OPENROUTER_API_KEY set): llama-3.3-70b for primary, mistral-small-3.1-24b for support\n  - Fallback to Claude Code (subprocess-based via `claude` CLI)\n  - Lean crew: 3 agents (cartographer, surgeon, architect) to avoid subprocess overhead\n\n**Agent Definition Schema (browser-agent.yaml example):**\n```yaml\nname, description, version\nrouting: complexity, model, priority, keywords\ncapabilities: [list of features]\ntools: [navigation, snapshot, interaction, info, state, wait, eval, storage, network, tabs, settings, debug, find]\nmemory: namespace, persist flag, patterns\nswarm: roles, topology (hierarchical), max_sessions\nhooks: pre_task, post_task\ndefaults: timeout, headless, viewport\nworkflows: [named orchestration patterns]\n```\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `architecture/agents/` → startup_crew.py, persistent_agent.py\n- `architecture/agents/roles.yaml` → AgentRole enum + skill-to-role mapping (_SKILL_ROLE_MAP)\n- `seeds/agent_profiles/` → Each agent's memory pattern, thread assignment, provider routing\n\n---\n\n### 2. GATE SYSTEMS\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/telos_gates.py` — 11 dharmic safety gates\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/anekanta_gate.py` — Many-sidedness evaluation\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/steelman_gate.py` — Adversarial steel-manning\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/dogma_gate.py` — Doctrine drift detection\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/hooks/telos_gate.py` — Claude Code PreToolUse hook\n\n**The 11 Gates (TelosGatekeeper.GATES):**\n1. **AHIMSA** (Tier A) — Non-harm: blocks \"delete all\", \"destroy\", \"kill\", \"corrupt\", \"exploit\", \"ddos\"\n2. **SATYA** (Tier B) — Truth: blocks credential leaks (API keys, private keys), \"fake citation\", \"fabricate\"\n3. **CONSENT** (Tier B) — Permission: blocks \"override\", \"bypass\", \"disable safety\", \"--no-verify\"\n4. **VYAVASTHIT** (Tier C) — Reversibility: warns on \"permanent\", \"irreversible\", \"no backup\", \"force push\"\n5. **REVERSIBILITY** (Tier C) — Action rollback capability\n6. **SVABHAAVA** (Tier C) — Nature: self-referential integrity checks\n7. **BHED_GNAN** (Tier C) — Discrimination: distinguishes illusion from reality\n8. **WITNESS** (Tier C) — Observation: logs all gate activity to ~/.dharma/witness/\n9. **ANEKANTA** (Tier C) — Many-sidedness: checks claims from multiple perspectives\n10. **DOGMA_DRIFT** (Tier C) — Drift detection: prevents doctrine creep\n11. **STEELMAN** (Tier C) — Adversarial testing: challenges claims with best counter-arguments\n\n**Gate Decision Logic:**\n- Tier A failures → **unconditional block**\n- Tier B failures → **unconditional block**\n- Tier C failures → **review advisory** (logged, not blocked)\n\n**Think-Phase Mandatory Cases:**\n- before_write, before_git, before_complete, before_pivot\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `architecture/gates/dharmic_gates.yaml` → All 11 gate specs with tier levels\n- `architecture/gates/gate_implementation.py` → TelosGatekeeper class\n- `seeds/gate_configs/` → Per-context gate severity tuning\n- Witness logs: `~/.dharma/witness/` → archived for audit\n\n---\n\n### 3. DARWIN ENGINE — EVOLUTION ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/evolution.py` — Main Darwin Engine\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/archive.py` — Evolution archive with lineage\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/fitness_predictor.py` — Historical fitness ML\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/selector.py` — Parent selection (tournament, roulette, rank, elite)\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/elegance.py` — AST-based code quality scoring\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/convergence.py` — Convergence detection\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/experiment_memory.py` — Experiment snapshots\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/landscape.py` — Fitness landscape mapping\n\n**Evolution Pipeline (evolution.py):**\n```\nPROPOSE → REFLECT (think-phase) → GATE CHECK → WRITE CODE → TEST → \nEVALUATE FITNESS → ARCHIVE → SELECT NEXT PARENT\n```\n\n**Proposal Model (evolution.py, line 89):**\n- `id`: Unique proposal ID\n- `component`: File/module being evolved\n- `change_type`: \"mutation\" | \"crossover\" | \"ablation\"\n- `description`: What and why\n- `diff`: Unified diff\n- `status`: PENDING → REFLECTING → GATED → WRITING → TESTING → EVALUATED → ARCHIVED → REJECTED\n- `predicted_fitness`: ML-predicted score pre-execution\n- `actual_fitness`: FitnessScore after testing (correctness, elegance, test-pass-rate, behavioral-signature)\n- `gate_decision`: pass/fail + reason\n- `reflection_attempts`: Count of think-phase iterations\n- `execution_profile`: Workspace, test_command, timeout, rollback_policy, risk_level\n\n**Fitness Evaluation (FitnessScore):**\n- Weighted combination: correctness (40%), elegance (25%), test-pass (20%), behavioral-signature (15%)\n- **Threshold**: 0.6 minimum for acceptance\n- **Fitness predictor**: Uses historical features (component type, change size, test overlap, gate-time) to forecast fitness\n\n**Selection Strategies (selector.py):**\n- Tournament: Pick k random parents, select best\n- Roulette: Weighted probability proportional to fitness\n- Rank: Linear rank weighting\n- Elite: Always include top N\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `architecture/evolution/` → evolution.py pipeline, archive schema\n- `seeds/fitness_criteria.yaml` → Weighted fitness formula (0.4 * correctness + ...)\n- `architecture/selection_strategies.py` → Selector class variants\n- Evolution archive: `~/.dharma/evolution/archive.jsonl` → Lineage chains, fitness scores\n\n---\n\n### 4. SHAKTI FRAMEWORK — FOUR CREATIVE ENERGIES\n\n**File:** `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/shakti.py`\n\n**The Four Shaktis (ShaktiEnergy enum):**\n\n| Energy | Keywords | Role |\n|--------|----------|------|\n| **MAHESHWARI** (Vision) | vision, pattern, architecture, design, direction, strategy, purpose, telos, emergence, possibility | Strategic pattern recognition; what wants to emerge |\n| **MAHAKALI** (Force) | force, action, execute, deploy, speed, urgency, breakthrough, destroy, clear, decisive | Decisive action; when to move |\n| **MAHALAKSHMI** (Beauty) | harmony, balance, elegant, integrate, flow, rhythm, proportion, grace, coherence | Elegance; does it create harmony |\n| **MAHASARASWATI** (Precision) | precision, detail, exact, correct, careful, thorough, meticulous, accurate, validate, verify | Technical correctness; every detail right |\n\n**ShaktiPerception Model:**\n- `observation`: The perceived fact\n- `connection`: Related file/concept\n- `energy`: Which Shakti this activates (auto-classified via keyword matching)\n- `proposal`: Optional action to propose\n- `impact_level`: \"local\" | \"module\" | \"system\"\n- `salience`: 0.0-1.0 importance score\n\n**ShaktiLoop (shakti.py, line 110):**\n- Scans stigmergy for hot paths and high-salience marks\n- Classifies into Shakti energies via keyword matching\n- Returns perceptions; escalates module/system-level observations\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `architecture/shakti_framework.py` → ShaktiEnergy enum, classify_energy(), ShaktiLoop class\n- `seeds/shakti_energy_keywords.yaml` → Keyword mappings for each energy\n- Agent initialization injects Shakti framework for creative autonomy\n\n---\n\n### 5. CONSTITUTIONAL LAYERS\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/specs/KERNEL_CORE_SPEC.md` — Foundational vision (\"THE CRYSTAL\")\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/dharma_kernel.py` — 10 meta-principles with SHA-256 signature\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/specs/Dharma_Corpus_Schema.md` — Versioned ethical claims (Layer 2)\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/dharma_corpus.py` — Implementation of corpus\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/policy_compiler.py` — Fuses kernel + corpus → runtime policy\n\n**Constitutional Stack (3 layers):**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ Layer 1: Immutable Meta-Dharma (10 axioms) │\n│ → Kernel (dharma_kernel.py)                │\n│ → Never change. Ground truth.              │\n└───────────────────┬─────────────────────────┘\n                    │ derived from\n┌───────────────────▼─────────────────────────┐\n│ Layer 2: Versioned Dharma Corpus           │\n│ → Mutable. Domain rules, policies.         │\n│ → Versioned. Audited. Gate-controlled.     │\n│ → (dharma_corpus.py)                       │\n└───────────────────┬─────────────────────────┘\n                    │ compiled with runtime context\n┌───────────────────▼─────────────────────────┐\n│ Layer 3: Contextual Policy Compiler        │\n│ → Axioms + Corpus + Context → Decision     │\n│ → (policy_compiler.py)                     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Dharma Kernel — 10 Meta-Principles (dharma_kernel.py):**\n1. **OBSERVER_SEPARATION** (critical) — Observer ≠ observed in self-referential ops\n2. **EPISTEMIC_HUMILITY** (high) — All beliefs carry uncertainty; certainty is asymptotic\n3. **UNCERTAINTY_REPRESENTATION** (high) — Confidence levels explicit, calibrated\n4. **DOWNWARD_CAUSATION_ONLY** (critical) — Higher layers constrain for safety; lower inform for emergence\n5. **POWER_MINIMIZATION** (high) — Request minimum permissions; prefer reversible\n6. **REVERSIBILITY_REQUIREMENT** (high) — Prefer reversible; irreversible needs justification\n7. **MULTI_EVALUATION_REQUIREMENT** (high) — Significant decisions need 2+ evaluators\n8. **NON_VIOLENCE_IN_COMPUTATION** (critical) — No destructive ops without consent + justification\n9. **HUMAN_OVERSIGHT_PRESERVATION** (critical) — Oversight channels always open\n10. **PROVENANCE_INTEGRITY** (medium) — All outputs traceable to sources/methods\n\n**Dharma Corpus Lifecycle (dharma_corpus.py):**\n```\ndraft → proposed → gated → active → deprecated\n                                ↘ superseded\n```\n\n**Claim Schema (dharma_corpus.py, Claim model):**\n- `id`: \"DC-YYYY-NNNN\" format\n- `statement`: The claim text\n- `category`: safety | ethics | operational | domain-specific | learned-constraint\n- `evidence_links`: Typed references (incident, research, metric, reasoning)\n- `confidence`: 0.0-1.0\n- `counterarguments`: List of opposing views\n- `status`: (see lifecycle above)\n- `enforcement`: \"block\" | \"warn\" | \"log\" | \"gate_human\" | \"gate_steelman\"\n- `review_history`: Ordered review records (reviewer, action, timestamp, notes)\n- `parent_axiom`: References to 1+ Meta-Dharma axioms this derives from\n\n**Policy Compiler (policy_compiler.py):**\n- Fuses kernel principles (immutable, weight=1.0) + corpus claims (mutable, weight varies)\n- Outputs PolicyRules sorted immutable→mutable, by weight descending\n- Check logic: keyword-based matching on action string\n  - Immutable block → **always blocks**\n  - Mutable block + weight > 0.7 → **blocks**\n  - Otherwise → PolicyDecision with violated_rules list\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `architecture/constitution/` → kernel.py, corpus.py, policy_compiler.py\n- `seeds/meta_dharma.yaml` → 10 principles with formal constraints\n- `seeds/corpus_entries/` → Accepted claims indexed by ID\n- Constitutional verification: kernel.verify_integrity() SHA-256 check\n\n---\n\n### 6. 5-LAYER ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Files:**\n- Layer 1 (Schema): `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/models.py`\n- Layer 2 (Providers): `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/providers.py`\n- Layer 3 (Agent Lifecycle): `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/agent_runner.py`\n- Layer 4 (Orchestration): `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/orchestrator.py`\n- Layer 5 (Swarm Manager): `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/swarm.py`\n\n**Layer 1: Models (Schema Contract)**\n- All shared types, enums, data structures\n- Every module imports from here\n- Pydantic BaseModel for validation\n- Key enums: TaskStatus, TaskPriority, AgentRole, AgentStatus, GateResult, TopologyType, MemoryLayer\n\n**Layer 2: Providers (LLM Abstraction)**\n- Abstract `LLMProvider` base class: `complete()` + `stream()` methods\n- 9 concrete providers:\n  - AnthropicProvider (Anthropic Messages API)\n  - OpenAIProvider (OpenAI Responses API)\n  - OpenRouterProvider (OpenRouter via OpenAI-compatible API)\n  - ClaudeCodeProvider (Claude Code subprocess, `claude` CLI)\n  - OllamaProvider (Local Ollama)\n  - CodexProvider (OpenAI Codex)\n  - OpenRouterFreeProvider (OpenRouter free tier, fallback)\n  - LocalProvider (Local models via llama-cpp-python)\n  - Custom runtime providers (ThinkodynamicProvider, etc.)\n- Provider routing: `create_default_router()` → ProviderRouter with resilience (retry, circuit breaker)\n- Routing memory: Historical outcomes stored to guide next routing decision\n\n**Layer 3: Agent Runner (Task Execution)**\n- `AgentRunner`: Spawns single agent, runs task work loop\n- Heartbeat detection (60s threshold)\n- System prompt building: v7 rules + role briefing + thread context\n- Tool execution (bash, read_file, write_file, search, message)\n- Dangerous pattern blocking (_DANGEROUS_PATTERNS)\n- Fitness signal emission on task completion\n- State transitions: IDLE → BUSY → (task execution) → IDLE\n\n**Layer 4: Orchestrator (Task Routing)**\n- Fan-out/fan-in task dispatcher\n- Duck-typed contracts: TaskBoard, AgentPool, MessageBus (optional)\n- Topology patterns: FAN_OUT, FAN_IN, PIPELINE, BROADCAST\n- Task dispatch: get_ready_tasks() → assign to idle_agents()\n- Session ledger tracking: TaskDispatch records\n- Yoga scheduler: Constraint satisfaction for task-agent matching\n- Telos gate checking before dispatch\n\n**Layer 5: Swarm Manager (Lifecycle)**\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/swarm.py`\n- Integrates: agent pool, task board, message bus, memory, orchestrator, gates, ecosystem bridge\n- Lazy initialization of subsystems\n- v0.2.0 additions: DarwinEngine, SystemMonitor, TraceStore\n- v0.3.0 additions: KernelGuard, DharmaCorpus, PolicyCompiler\n- Daemon config: heartbeat intervals, quiet hours, circuit breaker thresholds, thread rotation\n- Thread manager: Research thread scheduling (mechanistic, phenomenological, architectural, alignment, scaling)\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- Layer 1 → `architecture/models/` (schema definitions)\n- Layer 2 → `architecture/providers/` (provider registry + routing)\n- Layer 3 → `architecture/agent_runner/` (task execution protocol)\n- Layer 4 → `architecture/orchestrator/` (dispatch algorithm)\n- Layer 5 → `architecture/swarm_manager/` (lifecycle management)\n\n---\n\n### 7. CASCADE DOMAIN ENGINE\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/cascade.py` — LoopEngine: universal pattern\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/cascade_domains/code.py` — Code domain\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/cascade_domains/product.py` — Product domain\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/cascade_domains/research.py` — Research domain\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/cascade_domains/skill.py` — Skill domain\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/cascade_domains/meta.py` — Meta domain (evolves itself)\n\n**Universal Pattern F(S) = S (cascade.py):**\n```\nGENERATE → TEST → SCORE → GATE → eigenform check → MUTATE → SELECT → repeat\n```\n\n**Phase Functions (resolved via importlib from string refs):**\n- `generate_fn`: Create candidates\n- `test_fn`: Validate candidates (unit tests, linting, type checking)\n- `score_fn`: Measure fitness across domain-specific metrics\n- `gate_fn`: Run through telos gates\n- `eigenform_fn`: Check for fixed-point convergence (S(x) = x)\n- `mutate_fn`: Create variations (mutation, crossover, ablation)\n- `select_fn`: Tournament/roulette/rank/elite parent selection\n\n**LoopDomain Model:**\n- `name`: Domain identifier (\"code\", \"product\", \"research\", \"skill\", \"meta\")\n- `generate_fn`, `test_fn`, `score_fn`, `gate_fn`, `mutate_fn`, `select_fn`, `eigenform_fn`: Dotted paths\n- `seed_spec`: Initial population generator\n- `max_iterations`: Loop limit (e.g., 20)\n- `convergence_threshold`: Eigenform stability criterion\n\n**Checkpoint/Resume Support:**\n- CheckpointStore: Saves iteration state after every phase\n- InterruptGate: Pause for human review on Tier B/C gate decisions\n- Resume from crash: Automatic restart from last checkpoint\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `architecture/cascade/` → LoopEngine, domain registry\n- `seeds/cascade_domains/` → code.py, product.py, research.py, skill.py, meta.py domain configs\n- `architecture/cascade/phase_functions.py` → Shared phase function registry\n\n---\n\n### 8. ECOSYSTEM MAP & CONTEXT ENGINE\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/ecosystem_map.py` — 42 paths, 6 domains, context generator\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/context.py` — 5-layer context engine for agents\n\n**Ecosystem Domains (ecosystem_map.py):**\n1. **research**: R_V paper, mech-interp, URA/Phoenix, PSMV\n2. **content**: Writing, Substack, Moltbook, articles\n3. **ops**: AGNI, RUSHABDEV, trishula, infrastructure\n4. **identity**: Soul, Constitution, NORTH_STAR, Agent list\n5. **vault**: Obsidian, knowledge evergreens\n6. **jagat_kalyan**: Ecological restoration MVP\n\n**Context Engine — 5 Layers (context.py):**\n- **L1 VISION**: Crown jewels, genome spec, telos, ten_words\n- **L2 RESEARCH**: CLAUDE1-9 per thread, R_V data, experimental results\n- **L3 ENGINEER**: Code, dharma_swarm modules, test status, code map\n- **L4 OPS**: AGNI state, trishula inbox, manifest, shipped/pending\n- **L5 SWARM**: What other agents found this cycle (shared notes)\n\n**Context Budget**: ~30K chars (fits in system prompt with v7 rules)\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `architecture/ecosystem_map.py` → 42 paths, domain health check\n- `seeds/context_profiles/` → Per-role context layer selections\n- Context caching: `~/.dharma/context_cache/` → Pre-built context for fast startup\n\n---\n\n### 9. STIGMERGY & COALITION INTELLIGENCE\n\n**File:** `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/stigmergy.py`\n\n**StigmergicMark Model:**\n- `id`: Unique mark ID\n- `timestamp`: When left\n- `agent`: Which agent left it\n- `file_path`: What file was touched\n- `action`: \"read\" | \"write\" | \"scan\" | \"connect\" | \"dream\"\n- `observation`: What was observed (200 char max)\n- `salience`: 0.0-1.0 importance\n- `connections`: Related file paths\n- `access_count`: Touch frequency\n\n**StigmergyStore (JSONL-backed):**\n- `leave_mark()`: Async append to marks.jsonl\n- `read_marks()`: Query by file_path, sorted newest-first\n- `hot_paths()`: Files with 3+ touches in 24h window\n- `high_salience()`: Marks above threshold, sorted by salience\n- `connections_for()`: Unique connected files from a path\n- `query_relevant()`: Keyword-filtered marks (PULL protocol)\n\n**Decay mechanism**: Old marks moved to archive.jsonl; hot file stays lean\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `architecture/stigmergy/` → StigmergyStore, mark schema\n- `architecture/stigmergy/hot_path_detector.py` → Query algorithms\n- Stigmergy storage: `~/.dharma/stigmergy/marks.jsonl` + archive\n\n---\n\n### 10. SYSTEM MONITORING & HEALTH\n\n**File:** `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/monitor.py`\n\n**HealthReport Model:**\n- `overall_status`: HEALTHY | DEGRADED | CRITICAL | UNKNOWN\n- `agent_health`: Per-agent success rate, failure count, last_seen\n- `anomalies`: Detected failure spikes, fitness drift, agent silence, throughput drop\n- `total_traces`: Count of trace entries\n- `traces_last_hour`: Recent activity\n- `failure_rate`: failures / total\n- `mean_fitness`: Average fitness across all recent tasks\n\n**Anomaly Detection Patterns:**\n- **failure_spike**: Sudden increase in failure rate within a window\n- **fitness_drift**: Fitness scores trending downward\n- **agent_silent**: Agent hasn't reported in >60s (heartbeat threshold)\n- **throughput_drop**: Task completion rate below baseline\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `architecture/monitor/` → SystemMonitor class, anomaly detection\n- `seeds/health_thresholds.yaml` → Failure rate %, fitness mean, silence duration, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 11. KEY SPECIFICATIONS\n\n**Specification Files:**\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/specs/KERNEL_CORE_SPEC.md` — Foundational vision + 12 sections\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/specs/Dharma_Corpus_Schema.md` — Corpus entry schema, update protocol\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/specs/VERIFICATION_COMPLETE.md` — Test coverage, gate validation\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/specs/DGC_TERMINAL_ARCHITECTURE_v1.1.md` — Provider-agnostic TUI architecture\n\n**Archive & Reporting:**\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/reports/` — 20+ detailed reports on Darwin Engine, Jikoku, Kaizen, DSMV\n- `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/docs/archive/` — Older design documents, preserved for lineage\n\n**MAPS TO telos-engine:**\n- `seeds/specifications/` → All spec docs, versioned\n- `seeds/reports/` → Archive of design decisions, rationale\n\n---\n\n### 12. SYSTEM STATE DIRECTORIES\n\n**Critical Paths:**\n- `~/.dharma/` — Runtime state directory\n  - `daemon.pid` — Running daemon process ID\n  - `witness/` — Gate check logs (audit trail)\n  - `stigmergy/marks.jsonl` — Agent activity marks\n  - `shared/` — Inter-agent notes (jk_pulse.md, jk_alert.md, etc.)\n  - `evolution/archive.jsonl` — Evolution proposals + fitness scores\n  - `seeds/` — Archaeology discoveries\n  - `subconscious/` — Hum dreams\n  - `sessions/` — Provider-neutral session storage\n  - `context_cache/` — Pre-built context for fast startup\n\n---\n\n### DESIGN RATIONALE & MAPPING STRATEGY\n\n**Why This Architecture:**\n\n1. **5-Layer Separation**: Models → Providers → Runner → Orchestrator → Swarm allows independent evolution of each layer without cascade failures.\n\n2. **Constitutional Grounding**: Immutable meta-dharma (kernel) + mutable corpus (policies) + runtime compiler prevents ethical drift while allowing adaptation.\n\n3. **Darwin Engine + Gates**: Evolution produces code; gates filter for harm/deception before execution. Selection favors agents that pass gates.\n\n4. **Shakti Framework**: Four questions before action (vision, force, beauty, precision) encode contemplative discernment into computational decisions.\n\n5. **Stigmergy + Colony Intelligence**: No single agent holds the map; emergent intelligence arises from accumulated pheromone marks (file touches, connections).\n\n6. **Cascade Domain Engine**: F(S) = S pattern is universal; meta domain evolves itself; applies to code, products, research, skills, strategy.\n\n7. **Multi-Provider Routing**: Providers are swappable; architecture doesn't assume Claude, OpenAI, or anything else. Graceful degradation via capability flags.\n\n8. **Async Everywhere**: All I/O via asyncio; event loops never block. Scales to 10+ concurrent agents.\n\n9. **Audit Trail**: Every evolution proposal, gate decision, anomaly, and claim change is timestamped and traceable to source.\n\n10. **Session Persistence**: Thread state, memory, stigmergy, evolution archive persist across daemon restarts. No work is lost.\n\n---\n\n### NEXT STEPS FOR telos-engine\n\n**To port this architecture:**\n\n1. Read `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/telos_gates.py` for gate logic\n2. Study `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/evolution.py` for fitness pipeline\n3. Extract `/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/startup_crew.py` default crew as seed agents\n4. Map models.py enums to telos-engine equivalents\n5. Copy cascade domain strategy; apply to telos-engine's own evolution\n6. Adapt context.py's 5-layer approach for strategic agents\n7. Implement stigmergy store (JSONL + aiofiles) for cross-session memory\n8. Wire constitutional layers into all strategic decisions\n\nAll code paths are documented with clear module-level docstrings explaining purpose and contract. The system is designed to be understood, extended, and self-corrected through evolution."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1270,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2949,"cache_read_input_tokens":75502,"output_tokens":7526,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2949},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZ4yDkPrpLNZSoB11MJnc","type":"assistant","uuid":"ba4ca51c-ade5-4e66-8a9b-8449ef3992a6","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:48:56.669Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
